This is our current COMP DPS Support Druid build focusing on Healing, Cleansing, Alacrity, Regen, Protection and CC.
(This is a "custom build" that is different than the Meta Battle version.)
**You should be running THIS BUILD in our comp!!**

Staff ( Primary)
Sword/Warhorn (secondary mostly for Call of the Wild)
Relic: Relic of Antitoxin

**ROTATIONS**:

Ranged Spike:
- Call of the Wild on approach (axe/Warhorn T)
- Weapon swap to Staff (Mouse 4)
- Vine Surge (staff 4)
- Hunker Down (Siege Turtle Skill) (F3)
- Pump heals as necessary. Main Healing Sources: Staff 5 + Staff 3, Pet F3, Celestial Avatar 3/4

Melee Bomb:
(If no ranged spike)
- Call of the Wild on approach (axe/Warhorn T)
- Weapon swap to staff (Mouse 4)
- Vine Surge (staff 4)
- Celestial Avatar Rotation

Utilize your utilities and weapon skills as appropriate to provide healing/condition cleanse for the situation.

Celestial Avatar Rotation:
- Enter Celestial Avatar (shift + F2)
- Lunar Impact -> Seed of Life (cel 3 -> cel 2)
- Glyph of Unity / Glyph of Alignment -> Seed of Life (cel R + cel 3)
- Rejuvenating Tides (cel 4)
- Cosmic Ray (cel 1)
- Lunar Imact -> Seed of Life (cel 3 -> cel 2)
- Cosmic Ray (cel 1)
- When Celestial Avatar Ends, use Ancestral grace (staff 3)

Primary Heal Skills:
Ancestral Grace (staff 3)
Healing Spring (E)
War horn Skills (Regen) (T)
Glyph of Alignment (R)
Blast Finisher (Water Field) (R -> staff 3)
Rejuvenating Tides

Primary Condition Cleanse:
Healing Spring (E)
Glyph of the Stars (Out of Celestial Avatar) (G)
Blast Finisher (Light Fields) (T or E -> staff 3
Seed of Life (cel 2)
Frost Spirit (F)
Glyph of Alignment (R)
Shake It Off (Bear Skill) (F3)

() Seed of Life has no cast time, so it can be cast ANY time, including channeling and while cc'd. Primary cases being during Lunar Impact, which you can cast Seed of Life in the middle of to still get your quickdraw benefit on Seed of Life, but maintain a light field proc from the combination.

() Use Cosmic Ray until the next condition is met.

